\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 45. V. aznavourii} Dörfler,{\i  Herb. Norm.}{\b  48}: 244 (1907) ({\i V. pontica} Velen., non (Rupr. ex Boiss.) Wettst.,{\i  V. pumila} E. D. Clarke, non Ail.). Glandular-pubescent. Stem 5-15 cm, with suberect branches from the base. Leaves 3-12 mm, petiolate, the middle cauline deeply pinnatifid, with cuneate, distally toothed segments, the upper cauline and lower bracts more or less pinnatifid. Flowers in racemes; pedicels 1½-3 times as long as bracts, ascending. Calyx-segments 3-5 mm, ovate-lanceolate. Corolla 7-10 mm in diameter, blue. Capsule c. 4 × 5 mm, obcordate reniform, deeply 2-lobed, glandular-hairy; style 3-4 mm, exceeding the sinus. Seeds 1·2-1·5 × 1-1·2 mm, broadly ovate, very shallowly cup-shaped or almost flat.{\i  Dry grassland. • E. part of Balkan peninsula.} Bu Gr Tu.
\par

